cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.NE 

This paper is about improving spoken language understanding using a novel iterative delexicalization algorithm. The paper focuses on the application of this algorithm to RNN-based joint intent classification and slot tagging models. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new algorithm, which involves improving the delexicalization in every iteration based on model confidence, indicating that it could also belong to cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
